Do it all script launch_webserver.sh will install docker, images for our webserver and launch it on localhost.

MAKE SURE NO SQL SERVERS ARE RUNNING as there could be a conflict with Unix sockets.

Launch script tailored for ubuntu based Linux like for example, Mint.

With the instructions below, one could launch on anything that can run docker (theoretically).



Instructions to install our webapp into an apache image from scratch.

First install Docker Engine: https://docs.docker.com/engine/install/

Then download git repo. This file is in the repo so...
	git clone https://github.com/lenron/trustnet.git

Then run:
	sudo docker compose up -d

obf should now be up and fully functional at http://localhost:7800



